The paper deals with phase retrieval, which is a problem in signal processing and imaging. The paper proposes an algorithm that leverages finite rate of innovation sampling theory and sparse signal assumption to recover the phase information of a signal. This makes it likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Signal Processing (cs.SP), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
